TI  - Habitat changes and its impacts on the Caspian pond turtle (Mauremys caspica) population in the Golestan and Mazandaran Provinces of Iran.
T2  - Journal of Aquaculture Research and Development
M3  - Journal article
AB  - A total of 118 specimens ofMauremys caspicawere collected from 23 stations that included lakes, rivers, ponds, pools and fish farms in Golestan (n=72) and Mazandaran (n=46) provinces, Iran during 2011- 2012 to determine the impact of habitat changes on the turtle population dynamics. Results revealed that > 30% of specimens had necrosis and tissue destruction in the carapace and plastron. Sex ratio (male:female) did not significantly differ from 1:1. Population histogram showed a change in the population which could be attributed to the drought in the lakes and rivers of area. Water pollution due to the heavy use of agricultural pesticides and heavy metals, along with water acidity and presence of fungi were the potential causes for necrosis and tissue damages of carapace and plastron. The increase consumption of turtle eggs and its use as pet suggested the cause of population decline of this species.
