TI  - Key descriptors for Docynia indica(Wall.) Decne.
T2  - Key descriptors for Docynia indica (Wall.) Decne
M3  - Miscellaneous
AB  - Docynia indicais a versatile fruit tree belonging to the Rosaceae family. Naturally occurring at altitudes between 1000 and 3000 meters in Central and East Asia, this species thrives on sloping and degraded lands and has become increasingly popular in reforestation efforts. D. indicatrees, which can be semi-evergreen or deciduous, are resilient to forest fires, drought and frost, with fruiting requiring elevations above 1000 meters and cold winters. In highland agroforestry systems, D. indicais valued for its nutrient-rich and vitamin C-laden fruit, known for antioxidant properties and biological activity, making it a significant herbal medicine. The fruit is commonly processed into juice, wine, vinegar, syrup, jam and dried products, while the wood is used for household tools and fuel. The trees contribute to soil protection, improvement, and reforestation efforts by providing mulch material. Increasingly recognized as a vital source of income, particularly for smallholder farmers, D. indicasignificantly supports livelihoods and household incomes. Despite its benefits, there is a knowledge gap in optimal planting, harvesting, processing and marketing practices. This priority descriptor list, following the international standardized documentation system for genetic resource characterization, aims to aid in the study of the genetic and morphological diversity, conservation and domestication of D. indicaand the enhancement of its production and product utilization.
