TI  - Breeding report on the new upland rice variety of Jiaohan No. 1 with high yield and good quality.
T2  - Journal of Henan Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Yunnan japonica rice variety 22-2 was used as female parent and the local variety 68-11 was used as male parent to breed out a new upland rice variety named as Jiaohan No. 1 by Jiaozuo Academy of Agriculture and Forestry Sciences. This variety was examined by 2007-2008 national regional test of middle-late maturing upland rice in Huang-Huai-Hai area. The average annual output was 5 452.5 kg/ha, 22.9% higher than the control Handao 277. This variety also joined in the 2008 national productive test of middle-late maturing upland rice in Huang-Huai-Hai area. The result also showed yield increase, with average output of 5 638.5 kg/ha, 20.0% higher than the control Handao 277, and the variety ranked the second in the five tested varieties. This variety had characters of high yield, good quality, strong drought resistance, wide adaptability and easy threshing and was suitable for cultivation in Henan, Shandong, Jiangsu and Anhui provinces.
