TI  - Breeding of a new national certified early-maturing cotton variety Han 3206 and application of its diversified supporting cultivation technique.
T2  - Guizhou Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Objective: New early-maturing cotton varieties suitable for diversified planting modes were bred to provide the new ideas for the coordinated development of grain production and cotton industry. Method: Han 3206, a new early-maturing cotton variety, was bred successfully by using the new cotton line HS601(bred by Handan Academy of Agricultural sciences) as female parent and the transgenic insect resistant cotton Han 685 as male parent through the south propagation and north breed and directional selection. Result: The new early-maturing cotton variety Han 3206 was participated in the regional trial of early-maturing cotton varieties in the Yellow River Basin during 2019-2020. The two-year average yields of seed cotton, lint cotton, and pre-frost lint cotton were 3 547.5 kg/hm~2, 1 449.0 kg/hm~2 and 1 327.5 kg/hm~2 respectively, increasing by 7.7%, 10.2%, and 9.6% compared to the control variety Zhongmiansuo 50. Han 3206 had a growth period of 98 days, a compact plant type, and a thick stem. It was approved by Hebei Variety Approval Committee in 2021(Approval number: Jishenmian 20219001) and approved by National Variety Approval Committee in 2022(Approval number: Guoshenmian 20220028). Conclusion: Han 3206 with short growth period and vegetable(cabbage, broccoli and garlic) could be obtained better economic benefit by diversified supporting cultivation of double cropping system in the Yellow River Basin.
